 <description translatable="no">

    <p>
		EcoTubeHQ automatically plays highest quality / lowest bitrate YouTube videos, i.e. av1 codec videos are output by default, if av1 isn't available then vp9 is utilized, and if vp9 isn't available then h.264 is output. 	
	</p>
	<p>Features:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>EcoTubeHQ offers two video upscaling methods: 'Quality' and 'Powersave'. 'Quality' video output @720p is comparable to 1080p YouTube video quality.</li>
        <li>EcoTubeHQ can minimize CPU usage by utilizing Vulkan GPU Compute Acceleration during video output.</li>
        <li>EcoTubeHQ automatically opens low resolution YouTube videos [144p / 240p] in a small window. This can be used as a low bitrate miniplayer.</li>
        <li>EcoTubeHQ offers debanding to minimize video artifacts.</li>
        <li>EcoTubeHQ restricts 720p videos to 30fps.</li>
        <li>EcoTubeHQ offers drag and drop video playlists.</li>
        <li>EcoTubeHQ can play local video files with AMD FidelityFX Super Resolution.</li>
        <li>EcoTubeHQ offers two Opus audio bitrates for av1 and vp9 YouTube videos - 70kbps and 160kbps.</li>
      </ul>
 </description>
